headline: New York City’s Biggest Office Landlord Offers a Glimpse of the Market’s Comeback
summary: The largest owner of New York City office space suffered a surge in vacancy when the pandemic emptied out the city’s office canyons and the firm struggled to find new tenants.  Now, few investors are benefiting more from the office market’s budding recovery than  SL Green  White-collar workers are spending more time in offices.
